WEBVTT

00:56.686 --> 00:58.354
Easy, boy.

01:27.383 --> 01:28.760
Come on!

01:28.843 --> 01:29.928
Just run!

01:30.762 --> 01:31.971
Move.

01:32.847 --> 01:34.766
You're stubborn as old iron.

01:34.849 --> 01:36.392
He's twice the size of your last rider,

01:36.476 --> 01:38.269
and the field could be
just like this or worse,

01:38.353 --> 01:40.063
so you best get your feet under you.

01:42.107 --> 01:45.318
My father told me
you should never talk to a horse.

01:45.401 --> 01:48.571
He said they're dumber than dogs
and only understand the crop.

01:54.369 --> 01:55.537
But I don't think that's true.

01:56.538 --> 01:59.666
I think a horse doesn't
want to be ordered about

01:59.749 --> 02:01.417
any more than a man does.

02:04.379 --> 02:05.964
Ser Duncan only has us.

02:06.422 --> 02:08.882
And if he loses, he won't even have that.

02:10.175 --> 02:12.095
I can get the weapon in his hand...

02:12.971 --> 02:14.556
somehow.

02:15.640 --> 02:17.142
But then, it's up to you.

02:23.940 --> 02:26.608
Hyah! Go!

02:38.204 --> 02:40.999
Hyah! Yah!

02:42.834 --> 02:45.086
Hyah! Yah!

02:50.383 --> 02:51.384
Not bad.

02:51.467 --> 02:53.970
Ha! Go!

02:54.053 --> 02:55.889
Go, Thunder!

03:01.603 --> 03:03.229
Ser Duncan, take it.

03:04.105 --> 03:05.899
Ha! Go, Thunder!

03:12.697 --> 03:13.865
Take it quick, Ser Duncan.

03:13.948 --> 03:15.867
Go, Thunder!

03:15.950 --> 03:17.952
Whoo!

03:18.036 --> 03:20.205
Come on!

03:20.288 --> 03:24.042
Whoo!

03:24.709 --> 03:27.545
Good boy. Good boy, Thunder.

03:27.629 --> 03:29.589
Good boy.

03:29.672 --> 03:31.382
You steal that horse?

03:44.604 --> 03:47.523
Tell the truth. We'll be fair.

03:47.607 --> 03:50.485
It's not stealing
if you mean to put it back.

04:06.542 --> 04:08.044
What's wrong with your hair?

04:08.127 --> 04:10.088
What's wrong with your eye?

04:17.262 --> 04:18.303
Ahh!

04:24.686 --> 04:26.854
You're Ser Robyn Rhysling.

04:27.438 --> 04:29.691
You're the maddest knight
in the Seven Kingdoms.

04:29.774 --> 04:32.193
We are a vessel for the Warrior.

04:32.277 --> 04:35.863
When it is madness bid,
it is madness delivered.

04:37.657 --> 04:39.284
You're small for a squire.

04:39.367 --> 04:41.452
I serve Ser Duncan the Tall.

04:42.328 --> 04:44.289
He's large enough for the both of us.

04:45.999 --> 04:48.418
-We've not heard of him.
-You will.

05:05.184 --> 05:06.894
Where have you been?

05:06.978 --> 05:08.229
Training.

05:10.148 --> 05:11.983
Don't wander off without telling me.

05:16.779 --> 05:19.032
What are you doing, Ser?

05:19.115 --> 05:21.993
-Sewing a patch.
-Is that not my job?

05:23.036 --> 05:24.287
You know how?

05:27.665 --> 05:29.292
Then quit jawing and get the brushes.

05:29.375 --> 05:32.170
Thunder looks like he's been
dragged through a hedge.

05:32.253 --> 05:33.504
What about breakfast?

05:33.587 --> 05:35.465
There's salt beef after you're done.

05:36.632 --> 05:38.051
I'd sooner eat the horse, ser.

05:38.134 --> 05:40.553
You'll eat my fist
if you don't do as you're told.

05:49.979 --> 05:51.647
Never mind that.

05:52.774 --> 05:54.984
Yeah. Yeah, just like that.

05:55.068 --> 05:57.737
Keep it as close to the edge as possible.

05:58.321 --> 05:59.572
And that's your whipstitch.

06:00.656 --> 06:01.991
How'd you get it so even?

06:03.618 --> 06:07.163
Just, like-- just practice.
Just try again.

06:10.958 --> 06:12.710
-There.
-Yes!

06:15.421 --> 06:17.423
-Ser?
-Mm-hmm?

06:17.507 --> 06:20.009
Is it odd that I have black hair
growing out of my stones?

06:20.093 --> 06:21.803
It's odd that you're telling me.

06:24.722 --> 06:27.517
Prince Baelor was the first born

06:27.600 --> 06:29.977
Prince Maekar sprang out last

06:30.061 --> 06:32.813
Daemon was the bastard,
so they kicked his bastard

06:32.897 --> 06:36.484
Grass is green in summer,
green grass I adore

06:36.567 --> 06:39.862
But grass is red all over
when you kill a rebel

06:39.946 --> 06:41.614
Horses die in battle

06:41.697 --> 06:43.616
This battle was the front

06:43.699 --> 06:47.036
Blackfyre's not a trueborn,
he came from the wrong

06:47.120 --> 06:50.664
Country was in peril,
The Anvil was a rock

06:50.748 --> 06:53.876
The Hammer smashed the bastard
with his giant veiny

06:53.960 --> 06:57.755
-Host of Dornish spearmen
-It's time.

06:59.382 --> 07:01.426
-Fetch my armor.
-Now?

07:03.678 --> 07:05.680
Aye, now.

07:05.763 --> 07:06.764
Why?

07:08.474 --> 07:10.601
Because I mean to enter the lists.

07:10.685 --> 07:12.353
You don't have your shield.

07:15.690 --> 07:17.942
We'll-- yeah, we'll gather it
along the way.

07:18.025 --> 07:19.110
Mm-hmm.

07:19.193 --> 07:22.530
Also, the right of the first challenge
goes to knights of high birth and renown.

07:22.613 --> 07:25.616
Are you a knight
of high birth and renown, ser?

07:25.700 --> 07:29.704
Wait, so I cannot enter the lists today?

07:29.787 --> 07:34.083
Not today, ser, no.
Only knights of high birth and renown.

07:36.210 --> 07:38.629
Then why have I been vomiting all morning?

07:38.712 --> 07:40.006
It's a mystery.

07:46.846 --> 07:48.222
No, no, no, no, no.

07:49.974 --> 07:51.100
Goose eggs.

07:51.184 --> 07:53.102
Just the eggs.

07:53.186 --> 07:54.187
No, no, no.

07:55.021 --> 07:58.900
Shit, goose eggs, like...

07:59.609 --> 08:01.152
Just the...

08:02.403 --> 08:04.155
Thank you.

08:06.908 --> 08:08.576
Do you like goose eggs?

08:09.785 --> 08:12.455
Your shield will be ready
this evening, ser.

08:14.749 --> 08:15.917
Thank you.

08:27.553 --> 08:30.765
-Ooh, ooh! Ooh!
-Shut up.

08:57.833 --> 08:59.001
Mm!

09:02.255 --> 09:03.506
Mm!

09:08.553 --> 09:10.304
Come on!

09:10.388 --> 09:13.724
-Come on! Whoo!
-Whoo!

09:15.601 --> 09:17.144
-Why not?
-Come on!

09:29.073 --> 09:30.741
Come on!

09:31.867 --> 09:33.119
Whoo!

09:35.997 --> 09:38.374
Do you want some hard salt beef?

09:41.502 --> 09:44.255
Oh, I'm Egg. I can't eat hard salt beef.

09:44.338 --> 09:47.800
I just eat lovely food
and grapes and all the...

09:49.260 --> 09:50.803
Can't even drink a pint of ale.

09:50.886 --> 09:53.431
Yeah, 'cause it's disgusting.

09:53.514 --> 09:55.683
-It's not disgusting.
-Yes, it is disgusting.

09:55.766 --> 09:57.184
-It's not disgusting.
-It's disgusting.

09:57.268 --> 09:58.477
Well, then I won't buy you another one.

09:58.561 --> 09:59.562
Good.

10:03.608 --> 10:06.193
I think I could be quite happy
in a place like this.

10:08.112 --> 10:10.197
You're in a place like this.

10:10.281 --> 10:12.116
I meant for a while.

10:12.199 --> 10:13.451
Ah, yeah.

10:14.952 --> 10:17.413
After I lead a great
campaign for my lord, of course.

10:17.496 --> 10:18.706
Of course.

10:20.041 --> 10:24.503
I return a war hero and he gives me
a parcel of land for my very own,

10:24.587 --> 10:27.840
and the hand of his second
most beautiful daughter.

10:27.923 --> 10:29.342
Second most?

10:30.384 --> 10:33.346
Well, you've already
married the first most.

10:33.429 --> 10:35.097
Have you not, ser?

10:38.059 --> 10:41.395
I'd keep horses, plant oats and peas.

10:41.479 --> 10:44.148
-Raise cows.
-And lambs, perhaps.

10:44.231 --> 10:45.900
Fuck your lambs.

10:45.983 --> 10:50.071
Did you really ride all the way here
in the back of some farmer's wagon?

10:50.154 --> 10:51.906
I don't want to talk about it.

11:00.164 --> 11:01.582
I'll say this for you.

11:03.250 --> 11:04.960
You're a good worker
when you put your mind to it.

11:05.044 --> 11:06.545
Think so?

11:07.922 --> 11:09.048
Mm-hmm.

11:12.718 --> 11:15.846
Does that mean
I can stay on as your squire

11:15.930 --> 11:17.723
after the tournament?

11:23.854 --> 11:25.314
If I lose my first joust,

11:25.398 --> 11:27.817
I'll scarcely be a knight
after the tournament.

11:31.987 --> 11:33.447
But if you win?

11:41.288 --> 11:42.498
If I win...

11:48.212 --> 11:49.964
If I win, you can--

11:50.047 --> 11:51.841
Ser Duncan?

11:51.924 --> 11:53.718
A word, if you please.

12:01.517 --> 12:03.269
Is there an issue with my entry?

12:03.352 --> 12:05.813
Hm? Oh, no. No, I...

12:06.689 --> 12:09.024
I only wanted to show you
a new fishing spot I'm keen on.

12:13.654 --> 12:18.325
Ser Duncan,
I believe we are both men of honor.

12:18.409 --> 12:23.164
So, I hope you understand that what I ask
serves no private interest.

12:24.373 --> 12:26.417
Might it surprise you
to learn that my Lord Ashford

12:26.500 --> 12:28.836
has richly overspent
on his daughter's pageant?

12:31.005 --> 12:32.214
-It might not.
-Mm.

12:32.298 --> 12:36.886
Well, with winter not so long past,
and many of our flocks collapsed,

12:36.969 --> 12:38.679
hard times lay ahead.

12:38.763 --> 12:42.516
Unless we endeavor
to reverse our fortunes.

12:46.228 --> 12:48.606
I don't have any money, I...

12:51.567 --> 12:53.611
Shocking, that may be,

12:54.820 --> 12:57.782
I mean not to rob you, but to reward you.

13:00.451 --> 13:02.536
-Reward me?
-Aye.

13:02.620 --> 13:06.373
What do you know of
Lord Ashford's youngest, Sir Androw?

13:16.675 --> 13:18.010
He's a deft lance.

13:18.093 --> 13:19.261
Indeed, indeed.

13:19.345 --> 13:24.099
But were a challenger to come forth

13:24.183 --> 13:26.894
and unhorse Ser Androw, against all odds,

13:26.977 --> 13:29.688
the lucky few who backed
such an unlikely winner

13:29.772 --> 13:32.066
would find their pockets full.

13:37.988 --> 13:40.741
Now, now, rest assured.
Rest assured, I mean no disrespect.

13:41.617 --> 13:44.286
I ask only what you already intend.

13:44.370 --> 13:47.414
Drive your foe from his saddle
and take your place on champion's row.

13:49.333 --> 13:53.212
I do not want a victory
that I have not earned.

13:54.713 --> 13:56.215
Have you not earned it?

13:59.802 --> 14:01.929
Let Ser Androw take the fall,

14:02.012 --> 14:05.057
and you shall have his horse, arms,
and armor as recompense for your role.

14:06.058 --> 14:09.645
A tidy sum for a young hedge knight
who presently calls an alder tree home.

14:11.564 --> 14:12.773
It's an elm.

14:15.276 --> 14:16.277
Elm.

14:20.447 --> 14:22.199
I beg you, think on it.

14:22.283 --> 14:24.243
I shall seek your answer on the morrow.

14:26.787 --> 14:29.373
Perhaps the rains will hold till then.

14:30.916 --> 14:32.585
Mind your pride, Ser Duncan.

15:01.488 --> 15:05.451
Son of Meakar,
grandson to King Daeron the Good

15:05.534 --> 15:08.454
and Prince of House Targaryen,

15:08.537 --> 15:11.874
Prince Aerion Brightflame.

15:26.680 --> 15:27.765
Hyah!

15:42.988 --> 15:44.365
Cousin.

15:52.164 --> 15:54.792
Not to worry. I won't embarrass you today.

15:59.505 --> 16:01.173
Come out, come out, little knight.

16:03.050 --> 16:04.635
It's time you faced the dragon.

16:07.596 --> 16:08.847
Hyah!

16:45.467 --> 16:46.885
Hyah!

16:47.886 --> 16:50.014
Kill him. Kill him!

16:52.599 --> 16:54.560
Aww!

17:04.277 --> 17:05.320
Lance!

17:06.613 --> 17:07.613
Go!

17:12.745 --> 17:13.996
He's too low.

18:22.147 --> 18:24.274
-I want to leave.
-Aye.

18:31.949 --> 18:33.617
That was a terrible sight.

18:34.785 --> 18:36.912
But a squire must be strong.

18:36.995 --> 18:40.874
A mishap may befall me, and I'll need you
to keep your wits if it does.

18:41.875 --> 18:43.836
That was no mishap.

18:50.259 --> 18:52.344
The jousting is done for the day, I think.

18:53.512 --> 18:54.680
Come, lad.

18:56.807 --> 19:00.435
Oh! Alice was a special lass

19:00.519 --> 19:02.688
Born bereft 'er thumb

19:02.771 --> 19:06.441
Lost a digit tending flock,
now feeling awfully glum

19:06.525 --> 19:08.944
Oh! Alice with three fingers

19:09.027 --> 19:10.821
A copper in her glass

19:10.904 --> 19:12.656
Had two fingers less than most

19:12.739 --> 19:15.075
She'll shove them up your arse, hey!

19:15.159 --> 19:18.537
I once gave her a silver,
feeling down and lone

19:18.620 --> 19:22.082
I tried to buy a pinky,
but I got the whole arm bone

19:22.166 --> 19:25.961
Oh! Alice with three fingers
never had a lot

19:26.044 --> 19:27.921
She gave me all she had to give

19:28.005 --> 19:29.423
Two more than what was sought

19:29.506 --> 19:31.341
Oh! Two more than what I bought

19:37.931 --> 19:39.683
Do you suppose there was an Alice, ser?

19:41.768 --> 19:44.688
A crippled girl who shoved
her hand up men's arses?

19:44.771 --> 19:46.356
I think there probably was.

19:47.482 --> 19:48.901
Of course, there probably was.

19:50.110 --> 19:51.987
Do you think her name was really Alice?

19:54.656 --> 19:58.702
Mm, no. I just think Alice
is a nice name to write a song to.

19:59.870 --> 20:01.330
That means there was a cripple girl

20:01.413 --> 20:03.665
who was so good at pleasuring men
in their bums

20:03.749 --> 20:06.210
that they saw fit
to celebrate her in song,

20:06.293 --> 20:08.545
yet they could not bother
credit her true name?

20:08.629 --> 20:12.925
If there's a lesson in that,
it's for wiser men than me to say.

20:13.008 --> 20:14.718
Perhaps it is a story of honor.

20:15.969 --> 20:16.970
Honor?

20:18.055 --> 20:20.891
A misfortuned girl making
the best of her natural gifts.

20:22.309 --> 20:24.478
One might wish for more.

20:24.561 --> 20:26.647
But is this not the act
of a dogged spirit?

20:26.730 --> 20:28.440
Giving more than what is asked?

20:28.523 --> 20:30.192
"The whole arm bone," as it were.

20:31.693 --> 20:33.654
Perhaps her name does not matter, then.

20:33.737 --> 20:36.490
It's her story that abides.

20:36.573 --> 20:38.033
Her name is Hope, ser.

20:38.867 --> 20:40.535
Belongs to all who invoke it.

20:42.079 --> 20:45.707
Oh! Alice was a special lass

20:45.791 --> 20:47.751
Born bereft 'er thumb

20:47.834 --> 20:49.586
She lost a digit tending flock

20:49.670 --> 20:51.213
And now she's awfully--

20:55.926 --> 20:57.552
Did you ever know your father, Egg?

20:57.636 --> 20:59.054
Mm...

21:00.222 --> 21:02.349
No. Not really.

21:02.432 --> 21:04.393
Most like I saw mine hanged.

21:06.853 --> 21:09.564
There was a pot shop in Flea Bottom.

21:09.648 --> 21:12.651
I used to sell them rats and cats
and pigeons for brown.

21:13.652 --> 21:15.946
Cook there always said
my father was some thief.

21:17.698 --> 21:21.159
If he was as big as me,
he wouldn't have made a very good one.

21:33.588 --> 21:35.132
Say your fortune.

21:35.215 --> 21:37.259
Oh, yeah. Go on, then.

21:37.342 --> 21:40.178
You shall know great success
and be richer than a Lannister.

21:41.138 --> 21:42.931
Thank you. Do the boy now.

21:46.518 --> 21:48.020
You shall be king...

21:49.479 --> 21:53.400
and die in a hot fire,
and worms shall feed upon your ashes.

21:54.776 --> 21:57.529
And all who know you
shall rejoice in your dying.

21:58.488 --> 21:59.489
What?

22:03.160 --> 22:04.202
Thank you, that's very good.

22:07.372 --> 22:08.999
Why would she say that?

22:09.082 --> 22:11.209
Why would she say what? Come on.

22:15.547 --> 22:16.757
Ser Duncan!

22:18.050 --> 22:19.509
I saw you earlier with this boy.

22:19.593 --> 22:22.554
Yeah. This boy is my squire.

22:22.637 --> 22:25.432
Egg, this is Raymun Fossoway.

22:25.515 --> 22:26.767
Good day.

22:27.768 --> 22:29.561
See our show! It's great!

22:29.644 --> 22:31.772
Will you join me in my tent
for a cup of cider?

22:31.855 --> 22:34.232
I could wait at the puppet show, ser,

22:34.316 --> 22:36.485
and bring your shield
when the performance is over.

22:39.821 --> 22:41.114
We make it ourselves.

22:43.784 --> 22:44.868
Very well.

22:51.208 --> 22:53.168
Have you chosen an opponent yet?

22:53.251 --> 22:55.045
Oh, I'm not sure.

22:58.340 --> 23:00.342
Who does your cousin mean to challenge?

23:01.510 --> 23:02.969
If anyone's wounded on the morrow...

23:04.012 --> 23:06.014
I'm sure Steffon will be quick
to knock on his shield.

23:07.474 --> 23:09.643
He's about as chivalrous
as a starved weasel.

23:17.359 --> 23:20.654
I suppose Ser Androw and I
are quite equally matched.

23:20.737 --> 23:23.532
A local favorite.
You mean to play the villain?

23:25.659 --> 23:27.536
I heard Aerion were in
a spittin' rage at Lord Ashford

23:27.619 --> 23:28.995
for giving away his horse.

23:29.079 --> 23:31.206
Little comfort that will be
to Ser Humfrey.

23:31.289 --> 23:32.874
It looked as if he was
going to carry the day.

23:32.958 --> 23:34.543
Now his leg's shattered
like a baking dish.

23:34.626 --> 23:38.004
My squire thinks Aerion meant
to kill the horse.

23:40.715 --> 23:44.052
Just hard to accept that a knight
might be so dishonorable...

23:45.137 --> 23:46.304
let alone a prince.

23:46.388 --> 23:47.806
Why is that hard?

23:49.933 --> 23:50.934
No, I--

23:51.017 --> 23:52.769
They're incestuous aliens, Duncan.

23:54.396 --> 23:57.274
Blood-magickers and tyrants
who've burned our lands,

23:57.357 --> 23:59.192
enslaved our people,

23:59.276 --> 24:01.236
dragged us into their wars
without a mote of respect

24:01.319 --> 24:02.904
for our history or our customs.

24:02.988 --> 24:04.531
Every pale-haired brat they saddled on us

24:04.614 --> 24:07.200
has been madder than the last,
gods know how.

24:07.284 --> 24:09.953
The only honorable thing a Targaryen

24:10.036 --> 24:12.831
can do for this realm
is finish on his wife's tits.

24:12.914 --> 24:15.333
So aye, I think he meant
to kill the fucking horse.

24:24.009 --> 24:26.011
I got a bit carried away there.

24:30.182 --> 24:32.684
I heard that part
about the tits from Steffon.

24:44.029 --> 24:44.863
Excuse me.

25:00.128 --> 25:01.671
Wow.

25:38.458 --> 25:42.254
Aerion, he's all smiles and chivalry
as long as his father's watching.

25:42.337 --> 25:44.422
I saw Prince Maekar's chair was empty.

25:44.506 --> 25:47.425
He left Ashford this morning
to search for the rest of his misbegats.

25:47.509 --> 25:49.803
Misbegats? Which are those?

25:49.886 --> 25:52.931
His heir, Daeron, and the youngest.

25:53.014 --> 25:55.016
They departed Summerhall
together a few days ago,

25:55.100 --> 25:56.851
but never reached Ashford.

25:58.270 --> 26:00.230
There's rumors going about
that the boys are dead.

26:00.313 --> 26:02.649
Though most like Daeron,

26:02.732 --> 26:04.109
he's probably just drunk again.

26:06.778 --> 26:10.198
Little wonder Maekar's been walking around
like someone pissed in his swan pie.

26:10.282 --> 26:12.367
He's probably just worried about his sons.

26:12.450 --> 26:14.286
Seven know why.

26:14.369 --> 26:17.998
Daeron's a sot.
Aerion's just vain and cruel.

26:18.999 --> 26:20.709
The third's so useless,
they were gonna ship him off

26:20.792 --> 26:22.544
to a citadel to make a maester of him.

26:22.627 --> 26:25.171
-And the youngest--
-Ser! Ser Duncan! You have to come!

26:25.255 --> 26:27.465
-Aerion's hurting her.
-Hurting who?

26:31.261 --> 26:32.929
Stay back!

26:53.450 --> 26:54.326
Hold still!

26:54.409 --> 26:55.493
Hold on!

27:16.931 --> 27:19.392
Why did you throw your life
away for this whore?

27:21.353 --> 27:22.771
She's scarcely worth it.

27:25.148 --> 27:26.232
She's a traitor.

27:28.276 --> 27:29.736
The dragon ought never lose.

27:34.741 --> 27:35.909
Nothing more to say?

27:44.376 --> 27:45.877
You've loosened one of my teeth.

27:49.339 --> 27:51.299
So, we'll start by breaking out
all of yours.

28:03.478 --> 28:05.980
No! Don't touch him!

28:06.064 --> 28:08.274
-Ah...
-You stupid boy!

28:08.358 --> 28:10.151
Hold your tongue or they'll hurt you.

28:10.235 --> 28:11.695
-No, they won't.
-Watch out, please.

28:11.778 --> 28:13.446
-Excuse me.
-If they do, they'll answer to my father.

28:13.530 --> 28:14.864
Let go of him!

28:14.948 --> 28:16.991
Wate, Yorkel, do as I say.

28:19.953 --> 28:23.331
You impudent little rat.
What's happened to your hair?

28:23.415 --> 28:26.668
I cut it off, brother.
I didn't want to look like you.
